Edward Milton WALLACE v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 5487. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Nov. 16, 1956. Anthis & Gotcher, Muskogee, Okl., for appellant. Frank D. McSherry, U. S. Atty., Harry G. Fender, Asst. U. S. Atty., and Paul M. Brewer, Asst. U. S. Atty., Muskogee, Okl., for appellee.

Before BRATTON, Chief Judge, and PHILLIPS and LEWIS, Circuit Judges.

Dismissed for failure of appellant diligently to prosecute the same.
